  "texts": [
    "Random forest (RF)RF, developed by Svetnik et al. [42], is an ensemble recursive partitioning approach in which each recursive partitioning 'tree' is built from a bootstrapped sample of compounds, and each branch of a tree uses a random subset of descriptors [27].",
    "The following five hyperparameters were tuned to achieve the optimal RF model: n_estimators (10-500), criterion ('gini' and 'entropy'), max_depth (0-15), min_samples_leaf (1-10), and max_ features ('log2', 'auto' and 'sqrt').",
    "Naïve Bayesian (NB)NB classifier is developed based on Bayes' theorem [40] and widely used in molecular properties prediction and virtual screening (VS) projects [63][64][65][66].",
    "Two hyperparameters were optimized for NB models construction: alpha (0.01-1) and binarize (0, 0.5, 0.8).",
    "Support vector machine (SVM)SVM was formally developed in 1995 [41] and quickly became a mainstream ML method due to its excellent performance in text classification tasks [67]."
